The skeletal code confirms one important asymmetry: it builds render commands with a D3D9-style vertex window from the IBâ€™s min/max, but the IB values themselves are copied unchanged. Next Iâ€™m following those arguments through Graphics and the two backends to see exactly where D3D11 loses the range.
