34-// Phase 19 world-corruption DIAGNOSTIC (CODEX+Cursor ROUND-2 consult). Both
35-// AIs independently fingered the process-wide dynamic VB/IB ring + its
36:// unsynchronized static accounting (ms_used/ms_newFrame) as the #1 suspect
37-// for a live-only, RenderDoc-masked engine-transaction RACE. Smoking-gun test:
38-// log every ring lock that runs OFF the main/render thread. If this fires, an
39-// off-thread graphics transaction is confirmed (the hole the D3D11 runtime
40-// MT-lock does not cover). If it NEVER fires across a corrupt roam, the
41-// threading hypothesis is dead too. REVERT (set to 0) afterward.
42-//
43-// RESULT 2026-05-31: SILENT across a corrupt roam (896 ring unlocks, ~1M draws,
44-// 0 off-thread locks) -> CPU-thread race on the ring is DEAD. Next suspect: the
45-// CPU-races-GPU intra-frame WRITE_NO_OVERWRITE reuse hazard, which the thread
46-// audit cannot see (single CPU thread, but the GPU runs async). P19_DISCARD_ONLY
47:// forces WRITE_DISCARD on every dynamic VB/IB lock so each lock gets a freshly
48-// renamed buffer -> no overlap with an in-flight same-frame draw. Corruption
49-// VANISHES -> ring reuse hazard confirmed. Slow (many renames); diagnostic, REVERT.
50-// RESULT 2026-05-31: DISCARD-only ring = NO CHANGE -> dynamic ring EXONERATED.
51-#define P19_THREAD_AUDIT 0
52-#define P19_DISCARD_ONLY 0
