codex
One subtle point is emerging: `minimumVertexIndex`/`numberOfVertices` are not a clamp in the engine. They are a declared range derived from the same raw IB. If they span past `m_vertexCount`, D3D11 will happily fetch the zero tail; D3D9 gets that declared range in `DrawIndexedPrimitive`, but the real fix still belongs in the primitive/index generation, not in the backend.
